No domestic violence, robbery or rape cases have been opened with the police since April 8. The Middelburg Police did, however, receive four complaints of business burglaries. A burglary happened in the industrial area where a battery was stolen at Mokse Engineering, electrical appliances were stolen from a lodge on the N11 and another burglary occurred in Bhimy Damane Street. Alcohol valued at around R13 000 was stolen from Rondevouz Liquor store near Cafe 101.